latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Day three saw the launch of a coffee table book, "India in Fashion: The Impact of Indian Dress and Textiles on the Fashionable Imagination"—edited by Hamish Bowles and published by Rizzoli—by Nita Mukesh Ambani. Key contributors designer Anuradha Vakil, curator Amin Jaffer, journalist Suzy Menkes and author and editor Priyanka Khanna will read excerpts from the book at the Centre’s Studio Theatre.

2.30 pm - 3.00 pm

Panelists:
Amin Jaffer, art historian, writer and curator
Anuradha Vakil, textile and fashion designer
Suzy Menkes, fashion journalist and critic
Priyanka Khanna, editor and writer

#IndiaInFashion #NitaMukeshAmbaniCulturalCentre #CultureAtTheCentre

🚨US Premiere of India’s largest theatrical production at @lincolncenter, NYC!

Experience ‘The Great Indian Musical: Civilization to Nation,’ a spectacular tribute to India from 5000 BC until its independence in 1947.
An NMACC presentation conceived & directed by the legendary Feroz Abbas Khan, this show is not to be missed!

Limited run, 5 PERFORMANCES ONLY!

Yes, you heard it right! This September, #NMACCIndiaWeekend is coming to NYC @lincolncenter! 

From soul-stirring performances, music and dance to yoga, mindfulness, food, and fashion, we’re bringing the very best of India, its heart, its heritage to NYC.

Tickets GO LIVE on 26th June, stay tuned!

📍 Damrosch Park

Experience ‘Strings of Sarangi’ by Ustad Moinuddin Khan, Momin Khan & Pt. Aditya Kalyanpur, a concert tracing Rajasthan’s musical soul through stories of love, devotion, and celebration.

Rooted in tradition, the performance blends classical ragas, Rajasthani Maand, vibrant folk melodies, and soulful rhythms to evoke nostalgia, grace, and connection.

Join us on 27th June, 2025 at 8:00 PM at #TheStudioTheatre

Book now on nmacc.com

#CultureAtTheCentre

Doors are NOW OPEN for ‘Bhakti: Krishna’s Grace’!

Curated by Ashvin E. Rajagopalan and spanning across four floors, this exhibition traces the evolution of Indian culture, craftsmanship, and architecture — through rare artworks, larger-than-life installations, and interactive craft workshops.

SAVE THIS, it’s your next MUST-ATTEND exhibition!

🗓 Open till 17th August, 2025
📍Art House, NMACC

🎟 Book your tickets on nmacc.com

✨ The third edition of NMACC Bachpan is here– brighter, bolder, and bursting with joy!

DON’T MISS this one-of-a-kind celebration of the joys of childhood, packed with a super-fun line-up – from clown shows and puppet plays to radio jockeying, poetry jams, parent-child yoga sessions, and more.

Designed for children aged 1–14, this annual festival brings together playful learning, exciting performances, and interactive workshops for curious young minds!

🗓 July 19 – 27, 2025
📍 #NitaMukeshAmbaniCulturalCentre
🎟 Book your tickets now on nmacc.com

#NMACCBachpan #BachpanAtNMACC

A tribute, a transformation, a Kathak experience like no other!

Aditi Mangaldas’ ‘Uncharted Seas’ explores it all through the language of Kathak. Don’t miss this emotive, thought-provoking performance inspired by her legendary gurus!

🗓 July 11, 7:30 PM | 📍The Grand Theatre
🎟 Book your tickets now on nmacc.com

latestPosts.caption:
Bring home stories etched in time from the new pavilions of Swadesh by Reliance Foundation!

Odisha’s Pattachitra and Palm Leaf Engraving are two of India’s most visually arresting narrative art forms, bringing to life epics like the Ramayana and Mahabharata through vibrant natural pigments and intricate linework.

Visit us on the Ground Floor, NMACC, and celebrate India’s living artistic traditions!

#Swadesh #SwadeshOnline #MadeInIndia #RelianceFoundation #NitaMukeshAmbaniCulturalCentre
